{"title_page": "PM CARES Fund", "text_new": "\n\nThe '''Prime Minister's Citizen Assistance and Relief in Emergency Situations Fund''' '''(PM CARES Fund)''' was created on 28 March 2020, following the [[COVID-19 pandemic in India]]. The fund will be used for combating, containment and relief efforts against the coronavirus outbreak and similar pandemic like situations in the future. The [[Narendra Modi|Prime Minister]] is the chairman of the trust. Members will include the defence, home and finance ministers.\n<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.ndtv.com/india-news/pm-cares-pm-narendra-modi-announces-new-covid-19-fund-gets-rs-25-crore-from-akshay-kumar-2202275|title=PM Modi Announces New COVID-19 Fund, Gets Rs 25 Crore From Akshay Kumar|last=|first=|date=|editor-last=Roy|editor-first=Divyanshu Dutta|website=NDTV|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-03-29}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://newsonair.com/Main-News-Details.aspx?id=384047|title=People urged to donate generously in PM CARES fund; PM Modi says every contribution matters|website=newsonair.com|access-date=2020-03-29}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|last=|first=|url=https://www.business-standard.cm/article/current-affairs/pm-narendra-modi-announces-pm-cares-fund-to-fight-coronavirus-outbreak-120032900031_1.html|title=PM Narendra Modi announces PM-CARES fund to fight coronavirus outbreak|date=2020-03-29|work=Business Standard India|access-date=2020-03-29|url-status=live|others=PTI}}</ref>\n\nThe fund will also enable [[micro-donation]]s.<ref>{{Cite news|last=Sharma|first=Sandhya|url=https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/tech/internet/cyber-chiefs-warning-as-hackers-target-pms-covid-fund/articleshow/74877953.cms|title=Cyber chief's warning as hackers target PM's Covid fund|date=2020-03-29|work=The Economic Times|access-date=2020-03-30}}</ref> The minimum donation accepted for the PM CARES Fund is {{INRConvert|10||lk=yes|year=2020}}.<ref name=\":3\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.businesstoday.in/current/economy-politics/pm-cares-fund-better-suited-tto-deal-with-coronavirus-crisis-say-legal-experts/story/399670.html|title=PM CARES Fund better suited to deal with coronavirus crisis, say legal experts|website=www.businesstoday.in|access-date=2020-03-31}}</ref> The donations will be tax exempt and fall under [[corporate social responsibility]].<ref name=\":7\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.thehindubusinessline.com/economy/policy/donation-to-pm-cares-fund-to-be-fully-exempted-under-income-tax-act/article31221733.ece|title=Donation to PM CARES Fund to be fully exempted section 80G of I-T Act|last=|first=|date=31 March 2020|website=The Hindu @businessline|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-04-01}}</ref> The Prime Minister had said that the [[Prime Minister's Office (India)|PMO]] had received many requests to help in the war against COVID-19. Accordingly, the fund was set up and will be used for disaster management and research.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.dqindia.com/pm-cares-fund-need-know/|title=PM CARES Fund: All You Need to Know|date=2020-03-30|website=DATAQUEST|language=en-US|access-date=2020-03-31}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/politics-and-nation/pm-modi-announces-emergency-relief-fund-for-coronavirus-fight/articleshow/74863297.cms|title=PM Modi announces emergency relief fund for coronavirus fight|date=2020-03-28|work=The Economic Times|access-date=2020-03-31}}</ref>\n\n== About ==\nAny contribution made to the PM CARES Fund before 30 June would qualify for a [[tax exemption]] under (80G) [[The Income-tax Act, 1961|Income Tax Act, 1961]].<ref name=\":2\">{{Cite news|last=Noronha|first=Gaurav|url=https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/economy/policy/govt-clarifies-on-companys-contributions-to-pm-cares-fund-above-csr-limit/articleshow/74907220.cms|title=Govt clarifies on company's contributions to PM CARES Fund above CSR limit|date=2020-03-31|work=The Economic Times|access-date=2020-03-31}}</ref><ref name=\":7\" /><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/politics-and-nation/ordinance-issued-to-make-pm-cares-donations-tax-free/articleshow/74923420.cms|title=Ordinance issued to make PM CARES donations tax free|date=2020-04-01|work=The Economic Times|access-date=2020-04-01}}</ref> The [[Ministry of Corporate Affairs]] announced that contributions to the PM CARES fund would be counted as part of the companies corporate social responsibility with additional CSR being offset in subsequent years.<ref name=\":2\" />\n\n=== Contributions ===\nSeveral large business groups contributed to the relief fund, including [[Tata Sons]] and [[Sir Ratan Tata Trust|Tata Trusts]] ({{INR}}1,500 crore),<ref>{{cite news |title=Tata Sons' Rs 1,000 cr top-up takes group coronavirus fund to Rs 1,500 cr - India's biggest |url=https://www.businesstoday.in/current/corporate/tata-sons-announces-additional-rs-1000-crore-support-towards-coronavirus-fund/story/399506.html |accessdate=2 April 2020 |work=Business Today}}</ref> [[Wipro]] and [[Azim Premji]] Foundation ({{INR}}1,125 crore),<ref>{{cite news |title=Azim Premji\u2019s foundation, Wipro commit Rs 1,125 crore as India battles with coronavirus |url=https://www.financialexpress.com/industry/azim-premjis-foundation-wipro-commit-rs-1125-crore-as-india-battles-with-coronavirus/1916114/ |accessdate=2 April 2020 |work=Financial Express}}</ref> [[Reliance Industries]] ({{INR}}500 crore)<ref>{{cite news |title=Coronavirus Outbreak: Reliance Industries announces Rs 500 crore contribution to PM-CARES fund, |url=https://www.firstpost.com/health/coronavirus-outbreak-reliance-industries-announces-rs-500-crore-contribution-to-pm-cares-fund-8207531.html |accessdate=2 April 2020 |work=Firstpost}}</ref> [[ONGC]] ({{INR}}300 crore),<ref>{{cite news |title=Covid-19: ONGC contributes \u20b9300 crore from CSR to PM CARES fund |url=https://www.thehindubusinessline.com/news/covid-19-ongc-contributes-300-crore-from-csr-to-pm-cares-fund/article31209599.ece |accessdate=2 April 2020 |work=The Hindu Business Line}}</ref> [[Larsen & Toubro]] ({{INR}}150 crore),<ref>{{cite news |title=L&T donates Rs 150 crore to PM-Cares, commits to pay 160,000 contract labourers despite disruption in work |url=https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/industry/indl-goods/svs/engineering/lt-donates-rs-150-crore-to-pm-cares-commits-to-pay-160000-contract-labourers-despite-disruption-in-work/articleshow/74884470.cms?from=mdr |work=The Economic Times |date=30 March 2020}}</ref> [[Infosys]] ({{INR}}100 crore)<ref>{{cite news |title=Infosys Foundation commits Rs 100 crore to PM CARES Fund |url=https://www.techcircle.in/2020/03/31/infosys-foundation-commits-rs-100-crore-to-pm-cares-fund/ |work=Techcircle |date=31 March 2020}} </ref> [[Adani Group]] ({{INR}}100 crore),<ref>{{cite news |title=Gautam Adani gives Rsscx\n 100 crore to PM Fund to fight coronavirus |url=https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/politics-and-nation/gautam-adani-gives-rs-100-crore-to-pm-fund-to-fight-coronavirus/articleshow/74876443.cms |work=The Economic Times |date=29 March 2020}}</ref> [[JSW Steel Ltd|JSW Group]] ({{INR}}100 crore),<ref>{{cite news |title=JSW Group pledges Rs 100 cr to PM-CARES Fund for Covid-19 relief efforts |url=https://www.business-standard.com/article/companies/jsw-group-pledges-rs-100-cr-to-pm-cares-fund-for-covid-19-relief-efforts-120032900633_1.html |work=Business Standard India |date=29 March 2020}}</ref> [[Vedanta Limited]] ({{INR}}101 crore),<ref>{{cite news |title=Vedanta doubles its contribution to Rs 201 crore to fight COVID -19 |url=https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/politics-and-nation/vedanta-doubles-its-contribution-to-rs-201-crore-to-fight-covid-19/articleshow/74952721.cms?from=mdr |work=The Economic Times |date=2 April 2020}}</ref> ArcelorMittal Nippon Steel India ({{INR}}100 crore),<ref>{{cite news |title=COVID-19: Lakshmi Mittal announces contribution of Rs 100 cr to PM CARES Fund |url=https://www.business-standard.com/article/pti-stories/covid-19-lakshmi-mittal-announces-contribution-of-rs-100-cr-to-pm-cares-fund-120040100011_1.html |work=Business Standard India |date=1 April 2020}}</ref> [[ITC Limited]] ({{INR}}100 crore)<ref>{{cite web |title=Indian companies contributing to PM-CARES Fund to fight COVID-19 |url=https://www.investindia.gov.in/team-india-blogs/indian-companies-contributing-pm-cares-fund-fight-covid-19 |website=www.investindia.gov.in |language=en}}</ref> and [[Bharti Enterprises]] ({{INR}}100 crore).<ref>{{cite web |title=Bharti Enterprises pledges Rs 100 crore to help government fight against COVID-19 |url=https://www.aninews.in/news/national/general-news/bharti-enterprises-pledges-rs-100-crore-to-help-government-fight-against-covid-1920200406003520/ |website=ANI News |language=en}}</ref>\n\nBeside those above, some well known Indian firms have also contributed like [[Kotak Mahindra Bank]] and [[Uday Kotak]] ({{INR}}50 crore) {{INR}}25 each,<ref>{{cite news |title=Kotak Mahindra Bank, Uday Kotak jointly pledge \u20b950 crore to PM-CARES Fund |url=https://www.livemint.com/news/india/kotak-mahindra-bank-uday-kotak-jointly-pledge-rs-50-crore-to-pm-cares-fund-11585477616252.html |work=Livemint |date=29 March 2020 |language=en}}</ref> [[Asian Paints]] ({{INR}}35 crore),<ref>{{cite news |title=Asian Paints announces Rs 35 crores contribution to combat Coronavirus outbreak |url=https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/politics-and-nation/asian-paints-announces-rs-35-crores-contribution-to-combat-coronavirus-outbreak/articleshow/74896950.cms |work=The Economic Times |date=30 March 2020}}</ref> [[TVS Motor Company]] ({{INR}}25 crore),<ref>{{cite news |title=TVS Motor pledges Rs 25 cr towards PM's Relief Fund to fight Covid-19 spread |url=https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/magazines/panache/tvs-motor-pledges-rs-25-cr-towards-pms-relief-fund-to-fight-covid-19-spread/articleshow/74884435.cms?from=mdr |work=The Economic Times |date=30 March 2020 |language